  116. (* Execute a toplevel phrase *)

  118. let execute_phrase print_outcome ppf phr =
  119.   match phr with
  120.   | Ptop_def sstr ->
  121.       let oldenv = !toplevel_env in
  122.       Typecore.reset_delayed_checks ();
  123.       let (str, sg, sn, shape, newenv) =
  124.         Typemod.type_toplevel_phrase oldenv sstr
  125.       in
  126.       if !Clflags.dump_typedtree then Printtyped.implementation ppf str;
  127.       let sg' = Typemod.Signature_names.simplify newenv sn sg in
  128.       ignore (Includemod.signatures ~mark:Mark_positive oldenv sg sg');
  129.       Typecore.force_delayed_checks ();
  130.       let shape = Shape.local_reduce shape in
  131.       if !Clflags.dump_shape then Shape.print ppf shape;
  132.       let lam = Translmod.transl_toplevel_definition str in
  133.       Warnings.check_fatal ();
  134.       begin try
  135.         toplevel_env := newenv;
  136.         let res = load_lambda ppf lam in
  137.         let out_phr =
  138.           match res with
  139.           | Result v ->
  140.               if print_outcome then
  141.                 Printtyp.wrap_printing_env ~error:false oldenv (fun () ->
  142.                   match str.str_items with
  143.                   | [] -> Ophr_signature []
  144.                   | _ ->
  145.                       match find_eval_phrase str with
  146.                       | Some (exp, _, _) ->
  147.                         let outv = outval_of_value newenv v exp.exp_type in
  148.                         let ty = Printtyp.tree_of_type_scheme exp.exp_type in
  149.                         Ophr_eval (outv, ty)
  150.                       | None -> Ophr_signature (pr_item oldenv sg'))
  151.               else Ophr_signature []
  152.           | Exception exn ->
  153.               toplevel_env := oldenv;
  154.               if exn = Out_of_memory then Gc.full_major();
  155.               let outv =
  156.                 outval_of_value !toplevel_env (Obj.repr exn) Predef.type_exn
  157.               in
  158.               Ophr_exception (exn, outv)
  159.         in
  160.         begin match out_phr with
  161.         | Ophr_signature [] -> ()
  162.         | _ ->
  163.             Location.separate_new_message ppf;
  164.             !print_out_phrase ppf out_phr;
  165.         end;
  166.         if Printexc.backtrace_status ()
  167.         then begin
  168.           match !backtrace with
  169.             | None -> ()
  170.             | Some b ->
  171.                 Location.separate_new_message ppf;
  172.                 pp_print_string ppf b;
  173.                 pp_print_flush ppf ();
  174.                 backtrace := None;
  175.         end;
  176.         begin match out_phr with
  177.         | Ophr_eval (_, _) | Ophr_signature _ -> true
  178.         | Ophr_exception _ -> false
  179.         end
  180.       with x ->
  181.         toplevel_env := oldenv; raise x
  182.       end
  183.   | Ptop_dir {pdir_name = {Location.txt = dir_name}; pdir_arg } ->
  184.       try_run_directive ppf dir_name pdir_arg

  213. (* This is basically Dynlink.Bytecode.run with no digest *)
  214. let load_compunit ic filename ppf compunit =

  216.   seek_in ic compunit.cu_pos;
  217.   let code_size = compunit.cu_codesize + 8 in

  221.   LongString.blit_string "\000\000\000\001\000\000\000" 0
  222.                      code (compunit.cu_codesize + 1) 7;
  223. ‌  let initial_symtable = Symtable.current_state() in
  224.   Symtable.patch_object code compunit.cu_reloc;
  225.   Symtable.update_global_table();

  230.       [| input_value ic |]
  231.     end in
  232.   begin try

  234.     let _bytecode, closure = Meta.reify_bytecode code events None in
  235.     ignore (closure ());
  236.     may_trace := false;

  239.     may_trace := false;

  243.   end

  245. ‌let rec load_file recursive ppf name =

  257. and really_load_file recursive ppf name filename ic =
  258.   let buffer = really_input_string ic (String.length Config.cmo_magic_number) in
  259.   try
  260.     if buffer = Config.cmo_magic_number then begin

  264.       if recursive then

  266.           (function
  267.             | (Reloc_getglobal id, _)
  268.               when not (Symtable.is_global_defined id) ->
  269. ‌                let file = Ident.name id ^ ".cmo" in
  270.                 begin match Load_path.find_uncap file with
  271.                 | exception Not_found -> ()

  274.                 end
  275.             | _ -> ()
  276.           )
  277.           cu.cu_reloc;
  278.       load_compunit ic filename ppf cu;
  279.       true
  280.     end else
  281.       if buffer = Config.cma_magic_number then begin
  282. ‌        let toc_pos = input_binary_int ic in  (* Go to table of contents *)

  284. ‌        let lib = (input_value ic : library) in

  289.             with Failure reason ->
  290.               fprintf ppf

  292.                 name reason;
  293.               raise Load_failed)
  294.           lib.lib_dllibs;

  296.         true
